Web status monitor.
===================================
This script is to report via twitter when the http status code of a webpage is different of 200.

The main script is monitoring/report_status.sh


Instructions:

1. Modify monitoring/report_status.sh acording to you needs. The main data to change is the
   web page and the users that will be notified
2. Run ttytter/1.1.11.txt or the current version. Please sure that it work, send 
   messages to twitter, mentions and dm, remember to send dm both user must be followers.
3. When ttytter is working just call monitoring/report_status.sh
4. You can put this in a cron with: crontab -e 

Dependecies:

curl
gawk
ttytter -- in the repository

In debian and ubuntu just install with this:
sudo apt-get install curl
sudo apt-get gawk

